{"hero":True,"sub":"Devices & Launches","h3":"Nvidia unveils RTX Spark superchip to challenge Intel and AMD in laptops","summary":"Nvidia revealed a Windows PC chip pairing an Arm CPU with a Blackwell GPU, aiming squarely at the laptop processors made by Intel and AMD.","body":["The RTX Spark Superchip packs up to 20 Arm CPU cores, a Blackwell GPU with 6,144 CUDA cores and 128GB of unified memory, bringing the full CUDA software stack to thin Windows machines for the first time. Co-developed with Microsoft, the platform is pitched as turning Windows into an agentic AI operating system.","The first wave of laptops and compact desktops ships in fall 2026 from Asus, Dell, HP, Lenovo, Microsoft Surface and MSI. Analyst estimates point to higher-tier configurations near 2,899 dollars, with the news sending Intel and AMD shares lower."],"sources":[("Tom's Hardware","https://www.tomshardware.com/laptops/nvidia-unveils-rtx-spark-superchip-at-computex-2026"),("CNBC","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/05/31/nvidias-new-chip-to-power-fresh-line-of-windows-laptops-by-dell-hp.html")]},
{"sub":"EVs & Mobility","h3":"Rivian begins R2 deliveries as it chases Tesla's Model Y","summary":"Rivian started handing over its more affordable R2 SUV, opening with a performance trim and targeting up to 25,000 deliveries this year.","body":["Deliveries open with the R2 Performance with Launch Package at 57,990 dollars, pairing dual-motor all-wheel drive with 656 horsepower and up to 330 miles of EPA-estimated range. Rivian is prioritizing existing R1 owners for the first invitations before working through the broader reservation list.","The company expects as many as 25,000 R2 deliveries in 2026 and positions the model as its bid to become a household name on par with Tesla. A future standard trim is expected to start around 48,490 dollars."],"sources":[("InsideEVs","https://insideevs.com/news/797123/rivian-r2-deliveries-begin-june/"),("CNBC","https://www.cnbc.com/2026/06/09/rivian-r2-suv-tesla-competition.html")]},
{"h3":"Tesla expands unsupervised robotaxi service across all of Austin","summary":"Tesla widened its driverless ride-hailing service to cover the entire Austin geofence, though the active fleet remains small.","body":["The expansion covers the full metro area in Austin, marking a notable geographic milestone for the unsupervised service. Tesla has confirmed the broader coverage even as the verified fleet sits around 39 vehicles, with most operating in Austin.","Tesla's most recent shareholder disclosures point to planned launches in Phoenix, Miami, Orlando, Tampa and Las Vegas, though no firm dates have been set. For now the service stays concentrated in Texas cities plus the San Francisco Bay Area."],"sources":[("Drive Tesla Canada","https://driveteslacanada.ca/news/tesla-robotaxi-austin-unsupervised-expansion/"),("Tesla Oracle","https://www.teslaoracle.com/2026/06/08/tesla-expands-unsupervised-robotaxi-service-to-the-entire-austin-metro-area-cybercabs-spotted-across-the-us/")]},
{"h3":"Rivian joins ChargeScape to bring cheaper home EV charging","summary":"Rivian partnered with the ChargeScape grid platform, letting owners tap utility programs for managed and bidirectional charging.","body":["ChargeScape connects vehicles to leading utilities including PG&E, Xcel Energy, Con Edison and DTE, allowing drivers to earn savings by charging during cheaper grid windows. Rivian joins Tesla, Stellantis and others already using the platform for managed charging.","The deal slots into Rivian's broader charging push, with its growing network now open to most non-Rivian EVs and all Rivian vehicles able to use Tesla Superchargers. Bidirectional support also opens the door to using parked cars for grid resilience."],"sources":[("InsideEVs","https://insideevs.com/news/798838/rivian-partnership-cheaper-home-charging/"),("Utility Dive","https://www.utilitydive.com/news/managed-bidirectional-ev-charging-advances-with-utility-automaker-support/823171/")]},
{"h3":"Solid-state battery maker Factorial debuts on Nasdaq after long-range test","summary":"Factorial began public trading following a merger, after a real-world test showed more than 745 miles of range from its solid-state cells.","body":["The merger is valued at roughly 1.3 billion dollars, with Factorial set to receive around 110 million dollars in gross proceeds to fund commercialization. The company says its solid-state cells could power production EVs as soon as 2027.","The listing lands as the wider industry hunts for next-generation chemistries. Rivals like CATL are pushing sodium-ion cells toward mass production, while Hyundai has touted simpler solid-state designs that use cheaper metals."],"sources":[("Electrek","https://electrek.co/2026/06/08/solid-state-ev-battery-maker-joins-nasdaq-after-745-mi-range-test/")]},
{"sub":"Software & Services","h3":"OpenAI launches scheduled tasks in ChatGPT","summary":"ChatGPT gained a scheduled tasks feature, giving paid users automated reminders and recurring web or app monitoring from a dedicated page.","body":["The new Scheduled page lets users view, edit, pause or delete upcoming automated actions in one place. Subscribers can set reminders, manage recurring work or create tasks that proactively check the web or connected apps.","The beta feature is limited to Plus, Pro and Team subscribers, who can run up to 10 active tasks at once. It rolled out on web, iOS, Android and macOS, with Windows support still to come and some capabilities like file uploads not yet supported."],"sources":[("OpenAI Help Center","https://help.openai.com/en/articles/6825453-chatgpt-release-notes")]},
{"h3":"Google ships stable Android 17 with floating app Bubbles","summary":"The June Pixel Drop brought the stable Android 17 build to 21 Pixel devices, headlined by a new multitasking feature called Bubbles.","body":["Bubbles lets users turn almost any app into a floating overlay window by long-pressing its icon, keeping it accessible while working in other apps. Android 17 also adds stronger live threat detection, app memory limits for better battery efficiency and the option to hide app names on the home screen.","The rollout reached everything from the Pixel 6 to the Pixel 10 Pro Fold at once. Gemini Intelligence is confirmed for the release but arrives later this summer, and only on select advanced devices."],"sources":[("Android Authority","https://www.androidauthority.com/android-17-stable-rollout-features-3675016/"),("Droid Life","https://www.droid-life.com/2026/06/16/android-17-update-pixel-phones-download/")]},
{"h3":"WhatsApp prepares to roll out usernames globally","summary":"WhatsApp is moving to let users message and call each other through unique handles instead of sharing phone numbers.","body":["The username system would let both individuals and businesses reserve handles, similar to identity systems on platforms like Instagram. The change is aimed at giving users more privacy by keeping their phone numbers hidden.","The feature is expected to roll out worldwide around June 2026. It arrives alongside a wave of Meta updates spanning Instagram fonts, trial Reels and football-themed experiences tied to the FIFA World Cup."],"sources":[("Croma Unboxed","https://www.croma.com/unboxed/whatsapp-usernames-feature-rollout-june-2026")]},
{"h3":"Microsoft pushes Windows toward an agentic era at Build 2026","summary":"At Build 2026 Microsoft outlined a Windows 11 update where a system service orchestrates local and cloud AI agents.","body":["The Windows 11 2026 Update, version 25H2, introduces an Orchestrator service that manages local and cloud-based agents across the operating system. CEO Satya Nadella framed the shift as an agentic era where AI agents become the primary interface for users.","Copilot is being repositioned from a standalone app into a unified platform spanning Windows, 365 and Teams. Microsoft also confirmed an Ask Copilot taskbar entry and added GPT-5.2 to Copilot Chat for faster answers and deeper reasoning."],"sources":[("Windows Forum","https://windowsforum.com/threads/build-2026-microsofts-windows-ai-models-copilot-super-app-and-dev-setup-reset.421337/latest"),("Windows Latest","https://www.windowslatest.com/2026/05/27/microsoft-confirms-ask-copilot-is-coming-to-the-windows-11-taskbar-in-mid-2026/")]},
{"h3":"Real-time call translation arrives in June Pixel Drop","summary":"Google's June Pixel Drop added real-time call translation that speaks each caller's words in their own voice on newer Pixels.","body":["The feature translates each side of a phone call as it happens, preserving the speaker's own voice for a more natural conversation. It is available on the Pixel 10a and other recent models.","The same drop expanded Gemini-powered photo editing, letting users describe an edit in plain language and have it applied automatically. The updates ride along with the wider Android 17 rollout reaching the full supported Pixel lineup."],"sources":[("Thurrott","https://www.thurrott.com/mobile/android/google-pixel/337467/google-releases-the-june-2026-pixel-drop")]},
{"h3":"Apple ships iOS 26.5.1 to fix iPhone charging bug","summary":"Apple released iOS 26.5.1 to resolve a flaw that left some iPhone Air and iPhone 17 units unable to charge over a cable.","body":["The fix addresses a bug that caused a small number of iPhone Air and iPhone 17 models to fail to charge with a wired charger when the battery was nearly drained. The prior iOS 26.5 release had added end-to-end encrypted RCS messaging between iPhone and Android.","Attention is already turning to WWDC, where Apple is set to preview iOS 27 with Siri improvements and groundwork for a future foldable iPhone. Beta builds of iOS 26.6 are also circulating among developers."],"sources":[("MacRumors","https://www.macrumors.com/2026/05/11/ios-26-5-features/"),("MacRumors","https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ios-26/")]},
